Definition: plant with fleshy roots and erect stems with narrow succulent leaves and one reddish-orange flower in each upper leaf axil
Example: southwestern United States; Indians once cooked the fleshy roots
Synonyms: flame-flower, flameflower, Talinum_aurantiacum, wildflower, genus_Talinum, m, plant, with, fleshy, roots, and, erect, stems, narrow, succulent, leaves, one, reddish-orange, flower, in, each, upper, leaf, axil, southwestern, United, States, Indians, once, cooked, the
Category: noun.plant
